> Marc>         I have to agree with Lulu. Cryptography is a very
> Marc> political science whose total context is political (other than
> Marc> as a hobby). It may be the only thing that deserves to be
> Marc> called "political science". Lets keep them together.
>
>I apologize for referring to the political discussion as "ranting".
>Personally, I find it very interesting myself.
>
>However, while the "context" of cryptography may be political, the
>science itself is not.  I think it is eminently reasonable to want a
>low-volume group for discussion of research issues alone, and I think
>"sci.crypt" is an eminently reasonable name for that group.

If you're going to make a new group, give it a new name.  "Sci.crypt" will
get all the traffic, because it is the root group.  A low-volume group
like "sci.crypt.research" will get less traffic, even if unmoderated, because
the name sounds more imposing.

Bruce
